description.narrative: (Mexico): .Throughout the implementation period for USAID's new 2020 - 2025 Country Development Cooperation Strategy (CDCS), the Mission will apply project and activity management tools to learn and adjust programming in pursuit of Mexico's Journey to Self Reliance. As a reflection of that learning and adaptation, USAID is integrating its rule of law, crime and violence prevention, human rights, anti-corruption portfolios, as well as elements of its natural resource management programming into a coordinated approach specifically targeted at reducing impunity. This new approach highlights the need for improved collaboration among different stakeholders to effectively capitalize on strategic relationships with the Mexican government, private sector and civil society, as well as adapting through learning in pursuit of our development objectives. ..In pursuit of Collaborating, Learning, and Adapting (CLA), CLA support services will foster a culture of CLA throughout USAID management practices contributing to improved and sustained results. CLA support services will focus on the enabling conditions of the CLA framework (the culture, processes and resources), and develop a more efficient, intentional and participatory environment in the Mission. CLA support services will develop the capacity of AORs/CORs and other Mission staff to better integrate and execute CLA in activity design and implementation, improve collaboration across offices and develop a strong culture of adaptive management...
